= MM Tools =

== Introduction ==
MM Tools is a tool to reflash/test MM firmware for Avalon4
     +-----------+
     |    APP    |<-- MM Tools
     +-----------+
     |   MM OP   |<-- MM Tools API
     +-----------+
     |    IIC    |<-- Base on AUC api or linux iic api
     +-----------+

== Firmware upgrade ==

== Core test ==
Test AUC one by one and run MM core test one by one
Take one AUC for example:
Step 1: Detect MM modules
Step 2: Run MM core test one by one
	Note: we must keep other MM working, when test one MM.
Step 3: Generate test report (json array)
	Format:
	[{
	  "AUC ID": "AV4-1",
	  "MM ID": "1",
	  "MM Ver": "401412-39242210",
	  "MM DNA": "0130935a61aa16d0",
	  "PG1": [
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000"
	  ],
	  "PG2": [
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000",
	    "0000-0000-0000-0000"
	  ],
	  "bad": 0,
	  "all": 2560,
	  "bad percent": "0%"
	}]

